The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques to improve the accuracy and flexibility of optical mark reading (OMR) systems for multiple choice questions (MCQ) within tests. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image registration and feature extraction. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as a convolutional neural network (CNN) and a classifier to recognize the class of each answer box. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the proposed system and the development of an easy-to-use graphical user interface, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
